==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from ''Matter of Totten'', [[w:Case citation|179 N.Y. 112]] (1904), the case decided by the [[w:Court of Appeals of New York|Court of Appeals of New York]] which established the legality of this practice.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|head=[[Totten]] [[trust]]}}

# {{label|en|legal}} A form of [[trust]] created where one party (the ''[[settlor]]'' of the trust) places [[money]] in a [[bank account]] or [[security]] with instructions that upon the settlor's death, whatever is in that account will pass to a named [[beneficiary]].

====Synonyms====
* [[Payable on Death account]]
* [[poor man's will]]
* [[tentative trust]]